# Fixture: non-protected-port. Mirrors `ufw status numbered` (ufw 0.36.x, Ubuntu 24.04).
# worker_cidr=10.0.0.0/24; an ALLOW from a non-worker source on a NON-protected port
# (9090/tcp, line 6) must never be pruned — only ALLOW IN on the TLS port or gdbstub range
# can match. The protected DENY rows (4,5) likewise stay (not ALLOW IN).
Status: active

     To                         Action      From
     --                         ------      ----
[ 1] 22/tcp                     ALLOW IN    Anywhere
[ 2] 16514/tcp                  ALLOW IN    10.0.0.0/24
[ 3] 47000:47099/tcp            ALLOW IN    10.0.0.0/24
[ 4] 16514/tcp                  DENY IN     Anywhere
[ 5] 47000:47099/tcp            DENY IN     Anywhere
[ 6] 9090/tcp                   ALLOW IN    192.168.99.0/24
